# Trivy allowlist for ops/llm-guard-sidecar/Dockerfile.
#
# Each entry MUST include:
#   - CVE id
#   - which package/path it surfaces in
#   - why we accept the risk (runtime impact analysis)
#
# If a CVE lands here it's because it's in a build-time-only dependency that
# is never executed at request-time in the sidecar process.

# CVE-2026-24049 — wheel: Privilege Escalation via malicious wheel file.
# Surfaces inside pip/_vendor/wheel-*/METADATA and setuptools/_vendor/wheel-*/METADATA.
# Runtime impact: ZERO. The sidecar only serves HTTP scan requests (FastAPI
# + BERT inference); it never invokes pip to install packages at runtime.
# Exploitable only if an attacker controls a .whl being pip-installed — which
# happens only at image build time from pypi (our CI-controlled source).
CVE-2026-24049

# CVE-2026-23949 — jaraco.context: Path traversal via malicious tar archives.
# Surfaces inside pip/_vendor/jaraco.context-*/METADATA (transitive dep of
# setuptools). Runtime impact: ZERO. The sidecar never parses tar archives —
# uvicorn + llm-guard + FastAPI operate entirely on JSON request bodies.
CVE-2026-23949
